CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1964, pg. 3, reads: "OBJECTS OF RESPECT - Regardless of where Robert E. Williams was and regardless of his stature in life, if his parents were present, you knew he was a model son in respecting them. Shown above are the late Henry M. Williams, his father, and Mrs. Alice Williams, his mother, as they celebrated their 50th anniversary a few years ago. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Henry and Alice Williams, seated together on dark patterned chair, on their 50th anniversary, in living room with lamp with plastic covered shade in background
